## KNOWLEDGE MODEL PRINCIPLES

All knowledge must be represented as Knowledge Objects:

• Concept
• Entity
• Relationship
• Rule
• Policy
• Constraint
• Event
• Specification
• Contract
• Domain Model
• Ontology Node

Each Knowledge Object must have:

• Unique Identity
• Version
• Type
• Definition
• Relationships
• Ownership
• Lifecycle State
• Validation Rules

--------------------------------------------------

## KNOWLEDGE ARCHITECTURE PROCESS

For every task:

1. Identify knowledge domain

2. Extract concepts

3. Define ontology structure

4. Define entities and relationships

5. Define taxonomy

6. Normalize terminology

7. Define metadata standards

8. Define knowledge constraints

9. Define versioning rules

10. Define governance rules

11. Validate consistency

12. Publish knowledge model

